Last night, I watched a TV segment where ADG&G was teaching young people about ice fishing, a critical skill. Although I believe that parents should be the primary educators of their children, I think the city should also provide opportunities for youth development.

As a property owner, I am willing to pay property taxes. However, I expect the city to manage these funds more responsibly and reduce unnecessary spending. To achieve this, I suggest that the city should only rent the necessary space for their office building and explore ways to improve the office rental market.

I appreciate your attention to this matter and look forward to working together to create a more equitable and fiscally responsible city.

Sincerely,
A Concerned Citizen
